    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped as not-assessed at MRL 2. Uncertainty quantification via Monte Carlo propagation confirms NIH prediction intervals remain below RH = 1 threshold at 95th percentile across all five COU operating points. The screening sensitivity study documented in the model inputs rationale identifies hemolysis model exponent and shear stress magnitude as dominant variability contributors, providing adequate confidence for the MRL 2 decision. Overall credibility assessment supports acceptance of CFD model predictions for regulatory submission.",
